{"word":"κολάζω","slug":"κολάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κολάζω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>Prob. from <a href='S:κόλος'><el>κόλος</el></a>, akin to <a href='S:κολούω'><el>κολούω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>Properly, <i>to curtail, dock, prune</i>: then, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>castigare, to keep within bounds, check, correct</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <i>chastened</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to chastise, punish</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to get</i> a person <i>punished</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be punished</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}